reviews.review_text: Absolutely delicious food. Must try if you are around don paula. They have a good food menu and also fresh juices Thanks. I've added a few pics of the place for your reference. Their sambar with dosa was especially fantastic. Lip smackingly good.

Just your run of the mill Udipi cafe. The restaurant is maintained very clean. Quite tricky especially in the rainy season as there are stairs which are not planned well that is the only access point to the restaurant. The menu is all Udipi however there is inclusion of Goan bhajj pav, which is quintessential for any veg restaurant now. We ordered a Vada which I will not recommend, there was a typical smell of oil which revealed the oil used is not of good quality, the coconut chutney was runny. Tea was good and was served in a mud replica cup. I have had some snacks here before and everything served is very ordinary. But if you are looking for a decent vegetarian restaurant in the Dona Paula area you do not have much choice and might end up here again.

Good Place around Dona Paula, Carenzalem part of Goa to have Vegetarian food. This place specializes in Udupi food, since the people hailing from Udupi are running the restaurant. Tandoori Roti, Udupi Breakfast Items are good. Accepts card and UPI payments.
No designated Parking spot, Just have to park on either side of the main road. They use artificial colour for their few dishes. Service is good and fast. Don't go for the Kerala Parota here
